                          Installation instruction
                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

   MMEEC needs 'ssh' and 'scp' commands to work. Install an ssh-client
before install MMEEC and create keypairs to easy login to remote units:

   $ ssh-keygen
   $ ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub remoteunit1.lan
   $ ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub remoteunit1.lan
   $ ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub remoteunit1.lan

   After installation procedures, set path of 'ssh' and 'scp' commands,
and remote path of environment characteristics files in mmeec.ini.
(Search it /usr/etc/ or /usr/local/etc/). If you haven't got root level
access, copy this file to $HOME/.config/mmeec/ and edit it.


1. FreeBSD
~~~~~~~~~~
a. From binary (txz) package

   Use package manager to install/remove application.

b. From source package

   Build and install:
   # tar -xzf mmeec-0.1.tar.gz
   # ./configure
   # make
   # make install

   Remove:
   # make uninstall

2. Linux
~~~~~~~~
a. From binary (deb, rpm, txz) package

   Use package manager to install/remove application.

b. From binary (bin) package

   Install:
   # ./mmeec-0.1-i586.bin

   Remove:
   # /opt/mmeec/uninstall

c. From binary (tar.gz) package

   Install:
   # cp mmeec-0.1-i586.tar.gz /opt
   # cd /opt
   # tar -xzf mmeec-0.1-i586.tar.gz
   # cd mmeec
   # ./create_links
            or
   # tar -xzf mmeec-0.1-i586.tar.gz
   # cd mmeec
   # ./install

   Remove:
   # /opt/mmeec/remove_links
   # rm -r /opt/mmeec/
            or
   # /opt/mmeec/uninstall

d. From source package

   Build and install:
   $ tar -xzf mmeec-0.1.tar.gz
            or
   $ git clone https://github.com/pozsarzs/mmeec.git
   $ ./configure
   $ make
   # make install

   Remove:
   # make uninstall
